     <h3>RESTAURANT POLICY</h3>
     <p>1. Smoking is strictly prohibited.</p>
     <p>2. The customer shall observe and heed all safety precautions and warning signs issued by the management within the resort premises.</p>
     <p>3. The restaurants and their crews, and employees shall not be held liable for any injury, damages, or loss incurred by any person because of the consumption of the food and/or drinks brought into the resort, or resort food and/or drinks brought out of the premises without prior arrangement.</p>
     <p>4. The customer is requested to use the restaurant’s utensils and facilities with proper care. Any damage caused due to the fault or negligence of the guests shall be charged to their account.</p>
     <p>5.  The restaurant has parking spaces allotted for its guests. Drivers of the vehicles must present their driver’s license or any other form of government ID with security upon entry at the parking area of the resort. The resort assumes no liability for any loss and/or damages to the vehicles parked therein and to the valuables left inside the vehicles.</p>
     <p>6. Restaurant customers are obliged to make an effort to keep the surroundings clean. Guests should refrain from throwing rubbish anywhere other than the strategically located trash bins.</p>
     <p>7. Tricycles and other public motor vehicles which may transport guests to and from the resort are not in any way affiliated with the Restaurants. The resto shall not be liable for any loss, damage, or injury caused by or on the occasion of their use</p>
     <p>8. Restaurant customers are expected to behave in a manner not disruptive to the peace of the Restaurant and of the stay of another customer. The restaurant management reserves the right to ask misbehaving customer/s to leave the premises of the Restaurant.</p>
     <p>9. Bringing in fireworks, firearms, and other deadly weapons into the restaurant is strictly prohibited and violators will be dealt with accordingly.</p>

     <br>
     <h3>COVID PROTOCOLS</h3>
     <h4>Covid restrictions and safety protocols</h4>
     <p>A. Guests must complete a Health Declaration Form or present a vaccination card upon check-in.</p>
     <p>B. Body temperature checking using a thermal scanner at the resort entrances shall be undertaken for all guests by a qualified health or medical staff or trained hotel personnel. Only guests cleared during screening shall be allowed to enter the hotel perimeter to check in. Those with fever and flu-like symptoms will not be allowed to enter the establishment and will be referred to the doctor on duty, to the nearest hospital, or the Barangay Health Emergency Response Team (BHERT) by the DOH prescribed protocol.</p>
     <p>C. Guests shall be advised to disinfect their shoes using sanitizing mats provided at the entrances.</p>
     <p>D. Physical Distancing measures, hand hygiene, and respiratory etiquette must be observed when handling guests at the check-in counter.</p>
     <p>E. Guests must be informed of the management policies on room occupancy, dining, and use of public areas imposed to ensure safety and reduce the risk of infection. Physical distancing, wearing of face mask, proper handwashing/hand sanitizing practice must be emphasized.</p>
     <p>F. No showing of guests around the room after check-in. Guest escorting to the room may be allowed following the strict observance of physical distancing and in compliance with the health and safety protocols set by the DOH.</p>
     <p>G. Only single up to double room occupancy is allowed. Couples or family members who share the same household may be allowed in double or twin occupancy rooms. A distance of 1 to 2 meters between the beds is highly encouraged.</p>
     <p>H. During the stay, guests must strictly follow the following:</p>
     <p>------ 1. wear facemask when roaming around and if needed;</p>
     <p>------ 2. Proper disposal of used facemask;</p>
     <p>------ 3. Mingling with occupants of other rooms are not encouraged;</p>
     <p>------ 4. Practice proper handwashing etiquette/hand hygiene, respiratory etiquette, and proper use of facemask; and</p>
     <p>------ 5. Strict observance of Physical Distancing</p>

